current_commit_message: Change the way data are stored in assembly object
ImportFromMSH can now import the version 4.1 of msh file
- Remove mask from simcoon constitutiveLaw (tangent matrix is corrected) - some minor bug fixes

Fix 'tet10' and 'hex20' elements : - correct the shape functions for element 'tet10' and 'hex20' - number orders of shape function for import and export to and from msh and vtk files have been corrected

New : ModelingSpace is now attached to the WeakForm object and the derived objects (Assembly and Problem) ModelingSpace object have been modified and include now the elementary some generation of OpDiff object using the opdiff method.
- Add FE2 constitutive law and example
- Add WeakFormSum object to sum several WeakForm - Add 'Wm' as available output for problems
- Add a GetWm method to the FE2 constitutive law

- Change default NR error criterion to "Displacement" which is more stable than "Work". - The constitutiveLaw are now directly updated by the assembly object and not by the weakform itself - Other minor changes
- Add a sum capability for WeakForm objects - Add assembly_options dict in weakform object to specify default assembling options - Add HeatEquation WeakForm
Heat Equation weak formulation has been corrected
Add the possibility to use updated lagrangian method for non linear mechanical problems (nlgeom = 2) For that purpose, also update simcoon
Change some output variable names and associated label (name of the variable should be the same that the label used in resulting dict)
